context: As of the <a0_0><b4_0>2006<b4_0/><a0_0/> Census, there were 100,646 inhabitants in St. John's itself, 151,322 in the urban area and 181,113 in the St. John's Census Metropolitan Area (CMA). Thus, <b5_0>St. John's<b5_0/> is Newfoundland and Labrador's largest city and Canada's 20th largest CMA. Apart from <a3_0>St. John's<a3_0/>, the CMA includes <a1_0>12<a1_0/> other communities: the city of <b6_0>Mount Pearl and the towns of Conception Bay South, Paradise, Portugal Cove-St. Philip's,<b6_0/> Torbay, Logy Bay-Middle Cove-Outer Cove, Pouch Cove, Flatrock, Bay Bulls, Witless Bay, Petty Harbour-Maddox Cove and Bauline. The population of the CMA was <a2_0>192,326<a2_0/> as of 1 July 2010.
